Race.SummaryText:
Parishwide Proposition
(Millage)

Summary:  10 year, 3.55 mills property tax to acquire, improve, maintain, operate and support Parish Senior Citizens' Centers and to provide funding for Parish Senior Citizens' programs, services and facilities provided, or operated by, the St. Helena Parish Council on Aging.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of St. Helena, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy a special tax of three and fifty-five hundredths (3.55) mills on all the property subject to taxation within the Parish (an estimated $150,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year) for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2009 and ending with the year 2018, to acquire, improve, maintain, operate and support Parish Senior Citizens' Centers and to provide funding for Parish Senior Citizens' programs, services and facilities provided, or operated by, the St. Helena Parish Council on Aging?
